20   x = Symbol('x')

22   @public
23   class PolyQuintic:
24       """Special functions for solvable quintics"""
25       def __init__(self, poly):
26           _, _, self.p, self.q, self.r, self.s = poly.all_coeffs()
27           self.zeta1 = Rational(-1, 4) + (sqrt(5)/4) + I*sqrt((sqrt(5)/8) + Rational(5, 8))
28           self.zeta2 = (-sqrt(5)/4) - Rational(1, 4) + I*sqrt((-sqrt(5)/8) + Rational(5, 8))
29           self.zeta3 = (-sqrt(5)/4) - Rational(1, 4) - I*sqrt((-sqrt(5)/8) + Rational(5, 8))
30           self.zeta4 = Rational(-1, 4) + (sqrt(5)/4) - I*sqrt((sqrt(5)/8) + Rational(5, 8))
31

156      def l0(self, theta):
157          F = self.F
158          a = self.a
159          l0 = Poly(a, x).eval(theta)/F
160          return l0
161  
162      def T(self, theta, d):
163          F = self.F
164          T = [0]*5
165          b = self.b
166          # Note that the order of sublists of the b's has been reversed compared to the paper
167          T[1] = -Poly(b[1], x).eval(theta)/(2*F)
168          T[2] = Poly(b[2], x).eval(theta)/(2*d*F)
169          T[3] = Poly(b[3], x).eval(theta)/(2*F)
170          T[4] = Poly(b[4], x).eval(theta)/(2*d*F)
171          return T
172  
173      def order(self, theta, d):
174          F = self.F
175          o = self.o
176          order = Poly(o, x).eval(theta)/(d*F)
177          return N(order)
178  
179      def uv(self, theta, d):
180          c = self.c
181          u = self.q*Rational(-25, 2)
182          v = Poly(c, x).eval(theta)/(2*d*self.F)
183          return N(u), N(v)

187          return [self.zeta1, self.zeta2, self.zeta3, self.zeta4]
